# Pose Runtime — Windows .EXE build (Beginner-friendly)

## What you want
You want a **click-to-install .exe** so you don't deal with Node/npm.

This repo includes an Electron wrapper + electron-builder config.

### Easiest path (no local build): GitHub Actions builds the .exe for you
1) Create a GitHub account (free)
2) Create a new repository (empty)
3) Upload this project (drag & drop via GitHub web UI)
4) GitHub Actions will build the Windows installer automatically
5) Download the .exe from the "Releases" or "Artifacts"

## Local dev (optional)
- `npm install`
- `npm run electron:dev`

## Build Windows installer (requires dev tools)
- `npm install`
- `npm run electron:dist`
Output: `dist-electron/PoseRuntime-Setup-0.1.0.exe`

## API Key
The app lets you paste your OpenAI API key in-app (saved locally at `~/.pose-runtime/config.json`).
